India’s Sharma Leads Fightback in First Cricket Test Against England

-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 
2011-07-24T12:12:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/india-s-sharma-leads-fightback-in-first-cricket-test-against-england.html
Ishant Sharma took three wickets in
this morning’s session on the fourth day of the first cricket
Test against  England  to reduce the hosts to 72-5 at lunch.  England, which leads by 260 runs, was on 54-1 before
 Harbhajan Singh  trapped captain  Andrew Strauss  leg before wicket
for 32. Sharma then ripped through the middle order to dismiss
 Kevin Pietersen ,  Ian Bell  and  Jonathan Trott  at Lord’s in
 London .  Praveen Kumar took the wicket of opener  Alastair Cook .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 James Cone  at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  